        <trans-unit id="f933529d12a63f827169f14187c497d37d908102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>&lt;code&gt;scanf&lt;/code&gt; will then read the next char (that is, the newline) but not assign it to any pointer.</source>
          <target state="translated">&lt;code&gt;scanf&lt;/code&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt; leer&amp;aacute; el siguiente car&amp;aacute;cter (es decir, la nueva l&amp;iacute;nea) pero no lo asignar&amp;aacute; a ning&amp;uacute;n puntero.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;</target>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="cc7c3bf8e123d90d4454e06d240b02290f468268" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Another option (that I got from &lt;a href=&quot;https://faq.cprogramming.com/cgi-bin/smartfaq.cgi?answer=1352443831&amp;amp;id=1043284392&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;) is to read and discard the newline by using the &lt;em&gt;assignment-supression option&lt;/em&gt;. To do that, we just put a format to read a character with an asterisk between &lt;code&gt;%&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;c&lt;/code&gt;:</source>
          <target state="translated">&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;Otra opci&amp;oacute;n (que obtuve de &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://faq.cprogramming.com/cgi-bin/smartfaq.cgi?answer=1352443831&amp;amp;id=1043284392&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;aqu&amp;iacute;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt; ) es leer y descartar la nueva l&amp;iacute;nea utilizando la &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;opci&amp;oacute;n de supresi&amp;oacute;n de asignaci&amp;oacute;n&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt; . &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;Para hacer eso, solo ponemos un formato para leer un car&amp;aacute;cter con un asterisco entre &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;code&gt;%&lt;/code&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt; y &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;code&gt;c&lt;/code&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt; :&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;</target>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="046b39dee7fbf35f062765618aa86395d876dcbb" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>As I read in the C book, the author says that &lt;code&gt;scanf()&lt;/code&gt; left a new line character in the buffer, therefore, the program does not stop at line 4 for user to enter the data, rather it stores the new line character in c2 and moves to line 5.</source>
          <target state="translated">&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;Como le&amp;iacute; en el libro C, el autor dice que &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;code&gt;scanf()&lt;/code&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt; dej&amp;oacute; un nuevo car&amp;aacute;cter de l&amp;iacute;nea en el b&amp;uacute;fer, por lo tanto, el programa no se detiene en la l&amp;iacute;nea 4 para que el usuario ingrese los datos, sino que almacena el nuevo car&amp;aacute;cter de l&amp;iacute;nea en c2 y se mueve a la l&amp;iacute;nea 5.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;</target>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="825625d111b9b10f7717d1b26fd8039db163f2ee" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>However, does this only happen with &lt;code&gt;char&lt;/code&gt; data types? Because I did not see this problem with &lt;code&gt;int&lt;/code&gt; data types as in line 1, 2, 3. Is it right?</source>
          <target state="translated">&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;Sin embargo, &amp;iquest;esto solo sucede con &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;los tipos de datos &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;code&gt;char&lt;/code&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt; ? &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;Porque no vi este problema con &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;los tipos de datos &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;code&gt;int&lt;/code&gt; &lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;vertical-align: inherit;&quot;&gt; como en las l&amp;iacute;neas 1, 2, 3. &amp;iquest;Es correcto?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;</target>
        </trans-unit>
